Thanks for reaching out.  I understand the use case and think we can support it fairly easily.

`podman kube play` is making use of so-called pod exit policies.  Currently, there are two such policies (see [docs](https://docs.podman.io/en/latest/markdown/podman-pod-create.1.html#exit-policy-continue-stop)):
* "continue" - the pod will just continue running
* "stop" - the pod will be stopped when the last container exits. This is the default in `kube play` but since one container is still running, the systemd service will not be restarted.

To meet your use case, we could add a new policy (e.g., "stop-any" ?) that would stop the pod when any container exits.

Plumbing that into kube-play would probably require a podman-specific annotation (io.podman.pod.exit-policy ?) such that it can be shipped directly in the YAML.

@fpoirotte, does that sound right to you?

@rhatdan @umohnani8 @baude PTAL

@alexlarsson @ygalblum could that be of interest to your use case?
